<TITLE> Panel to review admin appts of BNP govt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 29 (bdnews24.com)  A six-member review committee has been formed to explore alleged irregularities in administrative transfers, promotions and retirements during the four-party alliance government, the establishment ministry said on Thursday. The committee, chaired by the prime minister's adviser Dr Alauddin Ahmed, will report to the government within 30 working days with its recommendations, according to the notice. Members of the committee include former secretary M Azizur Rahman and four additional secretary-level officials from economic relations division, law, home and establishment ministries. The ministry of establishment and other relevant ministries, divisions and autonomous bodies will help the committee in its work. The committee will also review the verdicts of appeals made to tribunals or the High Court by officials who allege they were victims of "irregular" transfer or retirement decisions. bdnews24.c
